SUMMARY:Supporting Survivors and Navigating Special Victims Cases
DESCRIPTION:The Protective Order Project (POP) is hosting a Special Victi
 ms Panel featuring professionals who work closely with survivors of domes
 tic violence and related harms.  Panelists include:&#160\;Jessi Hollingsw
 orth (Domestic Violence Victim Advocate)  Sally Thomas (Director of Victi
 m Resources at Indiana University)  Professor Valena Elizabeth Beety (htt
 ps://law.indiana.edu/about/people/details?name=beety-valena) (IU Maurer S
 chool of Law\, former victim advocate and scholar in victims' rights)  Pr
 ofessor Amy Applegate (https://law.indiana.edu/about/people/details?name=
 applegate-amy-g) (POP founder\, domestic relations mediator\, and expert 
 in domestic violence and family law)    The panel will bring together leg
 al and allied professionals to discuss their work supporting survivors\, 
 navigating the legal system\, and building careers in special victims ser
 vices.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The Protective Order Project (POP) is h
 osting a Special Victims Panel featuring professionals who work closely w
 ith survivors of domestic violence and related harms.</p><p>  Panelists i
 nclude:&#160\;</p><ul><li>Jessi Hollingsworth (Domestic Violence Victim A
 dvocate)  </li><li>Sally Thomas (Director of Victim Resources at Indiana 
 University)  </li><li>Professor <a href="https://law.indiana.edu/about/pe
 ople/details?name=beety-valena">Valena Elizabeth Beety</a> (IU Maurer Sch
 ool of Law\, former victim advocate and scholar in victims' rights)  </li
 ><li>Professor <a href="https://law.indiana.edu/about/people/details?name
 =applegate-amy-g">Amy Applegate</a> (POP founder\, domestic relations med
 iator\, and expert in domestic violence and family law)  </li></ul><p>  T
 he panel will bring together legal and allied professionals to discuss th
 eir work supporting survivors\, navigating the legal system\, and buildin
