SUMMARY:A Conversation with the Counselor to the Chief Justice of the Uni
 ted States
DESCRIPTION:The program will explore the unique role of the Counselor to 
 the Chief Justice of the United States. In this position\, Judge Robert M
 . Dow\, Jr. functions as the Chief Justice's chief of staff\, working clo
 sely with Court officers on Court-wide policies and initiatives. The Coun
 selor supports the Chief Justice as head of the federal judiciary\, worki
 ng in partnership with court executives and judges on matters of judicial
  administration\, and as liaison to the executive and legislative branche
 s on issues affecting the Court. The Counselor represents the Chief Justi
 ce in relations with judicial organizations\, foreign courts\, and visiti
 ng dignitaries. Judge Dow also supports the Chief Justice in his non-judi
 cial responsibilities\, including as Chancellor of the Smithsonian Instit
 ution. Judge Dow will be in conversation with Professor Andrew Hammond (h
 ttps://law.indiana.edu/about/people/details?name=hammond-andrew)\, who cl
 erked for Judge Dow on the U.S. District Court for the Northern District 
 of Illinois.Speaker bio:  Robert M. Dow\, Jr. has served as a United Stat
 es District Judge for the Northern District of Illinois since December 20
 07 and concurrently as Counselor to Chief Justice John G. Roberts\, Jr. s
 ince December 2022. Judge Dow served on the Judicial Conference Advisory 
 Committee on Civil Rules from 2013 to 2022 and the Advisory Committee on 
 Appellate Rules from 2010 to 2013. He has sat by designation on the Sixth
  and Seventh Circuits and is a member of the American Law Institute. He t
 eaches complex litigation at Northwestern University Pritzker School of L
 aw.  Before entering judicial service\, Dow was a partner in the Chicago 
 office of Mayer Brown LLP\, specializing in appellate litigation. Judge D
 ow is a graduate of Yale College (B.A. 1987)\, the University of Oxford (
 M. Phil. 1990\; D. Phil. 1997)\, and Harvard Law School (J.D. 1993). He c
 lerked for U.S. Circuit Judge Joel M. Flaum in 1993â€“94.  The Indiana&#1
 60\;Office of Admissions &amp\; Continuing Education approved this talk f
 or 1 hour of CLE credit.&#160\;  RSVP by noon on April 2nd to attend.&#16
 0\;&#160\;
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  The program will explore the unique rol
 e of the Counselor to the Chief Justice of the United States. In this pos
 ition\, Judge Robert M. Dow\, Jr. functions as the Chief Justice's chief 
 of staff\, working closely with Court officers on Court-wide policies and
  initiatives. The Counselor supports the Chief Justice as head of the fed
 eral judiciary\, working in partnership with court executives and judges 
 on matters of judicial administration\, and as liaison to the executive a
 nd legislative branches on issues affecting the Court. The Counselor repr
 esents the Chief Justice in relations with judicial organizations\, forei
 gn courts\, and visiting dignitaries. Judge Dow also supports the Chief J
 ustice in his non-judicial responsibilities\, including as Chancellor of 
 the Smithsonian Institution. Judge Dow will be in conversation with Profe
 ssor <a href="https://law.indiana.edu/about/people/details?name=hammond-a
 ndrew">Andrew Hammond</a>\, who clerked for Judge Dow on the U.S. Distric
 t Court for the Northern District of Illinois.</p><p><strong>Speaker bio:
 </strong></p><p>  Robert M. Dow\, Jr. has served as a United States Distr
 ict Judge for the Northern District of Illinois since December 2007 and c
 oncurrently as Counselor to Chief Justice John G. Roberts\, Jr. since Dec
 ember 2022. Judge Dow served on the Judicial Conference Advisory Committe
 e on Civil Rules from 2013 to 2022 and the Advisory Committee on Appellat
 e Rules from 2010 to 2013. He has sat by designation on the Sixth and Sev
 enth Circuits and is a member of the American Law Institute. He teaches c
 omplex litigation at Northwestern University Pritzker School of Law.</p><
 p>  Before entering judicial service\, Dow was a partner in the Chicago o
 ffice of Mayer Brown LLP\, specializing in appellate litigation. Judge Do
 w is a graduate of Yale College (B.A. 1987)\, the University of Oxford (M
 . Phil. 1990\; D. Phil. 1997)\, and Harvard Law School (J.D. 1993). He cl
 erked for U.S. Circuit Judge Joel M. Flaum in 1993â€“94.</p><p>  The Indi
 ana&#160\;Office of Admissions &amp\; Continuing Education approved this 
 talk for 1 hour of CLE credit.&#160\;</p><p>  RSVP by noon on April 2nd t
 o attend.&#160\;&#160\;</p>
