SUMMARY:Sherman Minton Moot Court Competition Finals
DESCRIPTION:Join us for the final round of the annual Sherman Minton Moot
  Court Competition.Case InformationJACOB LAWRIN\, in his individual capac
 ity as Chief Administrator and Commanding Officer of the Nuclear Bomb Loc
 ation and Security Team for the United States Department of Energy\, Defe
 ndant-Appellant v. MIKEY VALDEZ\, individually and on behalfof all simila
 rly situated plaintiffs.  The case involves residents of an off-the-grid 
 intentional community who were evicted and relocated by a federal governm
 ent agency that\, in an emergency situation\, used the community as a bas
 e of operations and sleeping quarters. The plaintiffs allege that their T
 hird Amendment rights were violated\, and that they should be able to bri
 ng the case as a class-action lawsuit.  The panel of judges includeJudge 
 Robert M. Dow\, Jr. (https://www.fjc.gov/history/judges/dow-robert-michae
 l-jr)\, Counselor to the Chief Justice of the United States and United St
 ates District Judge for the Northern District of IllinoisJustice Derek Mo
 lter (https://www.in.gov/courts/supreme/justices/derek-molter/)\, Indiana
  Supreme CourtMagistrate Judge Kendra Klump (https://www.insd.uscourts.go
 v/content/magistrate-judge-m-kendra-klump)\, US District Court for the So
 uthern District  Please RSVP below to attend in person. This event may al
 so be viewed live on the IU Maurer YouTube Channel (https://nam12.safelin
 ks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fc%2FIUMaur
 er&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Ccwbrowni%40iu.edu%7C7eeab435739d4f38596608de601c52
 3a%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4bcdd02510be91%7C1%7C0%7C639053871915141567%7CUnkn
 own%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRydWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4
 zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp\;sdata=If2OX8WsH0s
 5Ic%2BFWBBc62HCo7HQI8GaPn7fzFflGJE%3D&amp\;reserved=0). Registration is n
 ot required to view the livestream.
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join us for the final round of the annu
 al Sherman Minton Moot Court Competition.</p><p><strong><span style="text
 -decoration: underline\;">Case Information</span></strong></p><p><em>JACO
 B LAWRIN\, in his individual capacity as Chief Administrator and Commandi
 ng Officer of the Nuclear Bomb Location and Security Team for the United 
 States Department of Energy\, Defendant-Appellant v. MIKEY VALDEZ\, indiv
 idually and on behalf</em><em>of all similarly situated plaintiffs.</em><
 /p><p>  The case involves residents of an off-the-grid intentional commun
 ity who were evicted and relocated by a federal government agency that\, 
 in an emergency situation\, used the community as a base of operations an
 d sleeping quarters. The plaintiffs allege that their Third Amendment rig
 hts were violated\, and that they should be able to bring the case as a c
 lass-action lawsuit.</p><p>  The panel of judges include</p><p><a href="h
 ttps://www.fjc.gov/history/judges/dow-robert-michael-jr">Judge Robert M. 
 Dow\, Jr.</a>\, Counselor to the Chief Justice of the United States and U
 nited States District Judge for the Northern District of Illinois</p><p><
 a href="https://www.in.gov/courts/supreme/justices/derek-molter/">Justice
  Derek Molter</a>\, Indiana Supreme Court</p><p><a href="https://www.insd
 .uscourts.gov/content/magistrate-judge-m-kendra-klump">Magistrate Judge K
 endra Klump</a>\, US District Court for the Southern District</p><p>  Ple
 ase RSVP below to attend in person. This event may also be viewed live on
  the <a href="https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3
 A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fc%2FIUMaurer&amp\;data=05%7C02%7Ccwbrowni%40iu.e
 du%7C7eeab435739d4f38596608de601c523a%7C1113be34aed14d00ab4bcdd02510be91%
 7C1%7C0%7C639053871915141567%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJFbXB0eU1hcGkiOnRy
 dWUsIlYiOiIwLjAuMDAwMCIsIlAiOiJXaW4zMiIsIkFOIjoiTWFpbCIsIldUIjoyfQ%3D%3D%
 7C0%7C%7C%7C&amp\;sdata=If2OX8WsH0s5Ic%2BFWBBc62HCo7HQI8GaPn7fzFflGJE%3D&
 amp\;reserved=0">IU Maurer YouTube Channel</a>. Registration is not requi
 red to view the livestream.</p>
