SUMMARY:Operating While Intoxicated: Prosecution
DESCRIPTION:Join CrimSoc for an engaging discussion on the prosecution of
  Operating While Intoxicated (OWI) cases. This event will explore the leg
 al\, procedural\, and practical aspects of prosecuting OWI offenses\, inc
 luding charging decisions\, evidentiary issues\, field sobriety and chemi
 cal testing\, plea negotiations\, and trial strategy. Attendees will gain
  insight into how prosecutors evaluate and build OWI cases. This is a gre
 at opportunity for students interested in criminal law\, litigation\, or 
 prosecution to hear real-world perspectives and ask questions about handl
 ing one of the most common and impactful criminal offenses.&#160\;Tyler H
 olmes - Chief Deputy Prosecutor in Greene CountyChris Daniels - Senior Tr
 affic Safety Resource Prosecutor for the Indiana Prosecuting Attorneys Co
 uncil (IPAC)Trisha Bushey - Deputy Prosecutor in Monroe County
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  Join CrimSoc for an engaging discussion
  on the prosecution of Operating While Intoxicated (OWI) cases. This even
 t will explore the legal\, procedural\, and practical aspects of prosecut
 ing OWI offenses\, including charging decisions\, evidentiary issues\, fi
 eld sobriety and chemical testing\, plea negotiations\, and trial strateg
 y. Attendees will gain insight into how prosecutors evaluate and build OW
 I cases. This is a great opportunity for students interested in criminal 
 law\, litigation\, or prosecution to hear real-world perspectives and ask
  questions about handling one of the most common and impactful criminal o
 ffenses.&#160\;</p><ul><li><span style="font-size: 10.0pt\; font-family: 
 'Arial'\,sans-serif\; color: black\;">Tyler Holmes - Chief Deputy Prosecu
 tor in Greene County</span></li><li><span style="font-size: 10.0pt\; font
 -family: 'Arial'\,sans-serif\; color: black\;">Chris Daniels - Senior Tra
