SUMMARY:Docket Talk: What's at Stake at the Supreme Court
DESCRIPTION:From birthright citizenship to transgender rights\, the issue
 s facing the Supreme Court this year will have critical consequences with
 in and without the United States. Join ACS and our panelists in discussin
 g what's at stake in some of the most contentious cases on the docket. Fe
 aturing:  Professor Yvette Butler discussing LGBTQ+ rights and West Virgi
 nia v. B. P. J. and/or Chiles v. Salazar  Professor Jayanth Krishnan disc
 ussing birthright citizenship and Trump v. Barbara  Professor Rafael MacĂ
 ­a Briedis discussing free speech in campaign financing and NRSC v. FEC  
 Professor Steve Sanders discussing tariffs and Learning Resources\, Inc. 
 v. Trump
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  From birthright citizenship to transgen
 der rights\, the issues facing the Supreme Court this year will have crit
 ical consequences within and without the United States. Join ACS and our 
 panelists in discussing what's at stake in some of the most contentious c
 ases on the docket. Featuring:</p><p>  Professor Yvette Butler discussing
  LGBTQ+ rights and <em>West Virginia v. B. P. J.</em> and/or <em>Chiles v
 . Salazar</em></p><p>  Professor Jayanth Krishnan discussing birthright c
 itizenship and <em>Trump v. Barbara</em></p><p>  Professor Rafael MacĂ­a 
 Briedis discussing free speech in campaign financing and <em>NRSC v. FEC<
 /em></p><p>  Professor Steve Sanders discussing tariffs and <em>Learning 
 Resources\, Inc. v. Trump</em></p>
